This application must be web first but also support mobile through capacitor portability.

## Tech Stack
- Next 16.1.16
- React 19.2.3
- Capacitor 8.2.0
- Tailwind 4
- Typescript 5
- Ionic React Components 8.8.1

## Standards
- Always prefer to componentization
- Always check related or similar existing implementations before suggest or implement new one to avoid code duplicity or break code patterns
- Generic functions must be treated as utils and reutilized across the project
- Work modularized, grouping screens like backend domain separations
- API integration is done via orval and axios: use the orval-generated client (e.g. getVetShifterAPI()) where needed; do not add a separate API service layer
- This is an application for animal health area, so use light theme and colors that correspond to this environment 
- Prefer to use Ionic components for awesome interface on mobile after capacitor compilation
- Be careful about capacitor mobile compilation specific implementation details to avoid implementing something that work on only one environment. Everything must work on both.
